'''''Digital Champ: Battle Boxing''''' is a [[boxing]] [[video game]] developed and published by [[Naxat Soft]] for the [[TurboGrafx-16]]. The game was released on the [[Wii]]'s [[Virtual Console]] in Japan on April 15, 2008, Europe on May 16, 2008, and in North America on October 20, 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=Two WiiWare Games and Two Virtual Console Games Added to Wii Shop Channel|url=https://www.nintendo.com/whatsnew/detail/5eE1cnzPq40kQN4Gey4GeIRdIUlrEX8a|publisher=Nintendo of America|date=2008-10-20|accessdate=2008-10-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/wii/vc/software/07.html|title = Wii &#124; Virtual Console バーチャルコンソール}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.com/games/detail/KKqOWu8cRXvhlrPHr-jodd1NOGiRs9mV|title = Nintendo - Official Site - Video Game Consoles, Games - Nintendo - Official Site}}</ref> It was also released in the mid-2010s for the Virtual Console on the [[Wii U]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/titles/20010000011507|title=デジタルチャンプ &#124; Wii U &#124; 任天堂}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.com/games/detail/digital-champ-battle-boxing-wii-u|title = Digital Champ Battle Boxing for Wii U - Nintendo Game Details}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.uk/Games/TurboGrafx/Digital-Champ-1302273.html#Overview|title = Digital Champ}}</ref>

The game takes place in the fictional year 20XX, with the main player as a mutant fighting hordes of boxer clones before facing off against a robotic boxer. Three clone opponents exist; Marciano, Mick and Samson. Each match is a maximum of twelve rounds, each being three minutes.

